  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ACCOUNT EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>What you'll be doing</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintaining accurate and up-to-date financial records, including accounts payable, accounts receivable, bank reconciliations and general ledger transactions</li>\n  <li>Preparing monthly financial reports, such as profit and loss statements, balance sheets and cash flow statements</li>\n  <li>Liaising with clients, vendors and other stakeholders to resolve accounting-related queries and issues</li>\n  <li>Providing administrative support to the finance team as needed</li>\n  <li>Ensuring compliance with relevant accounting standards, tax regulations and internal policies</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What we're looking for</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of experience in a similar Accounts Executive or Bookkeeping role, preferably within a professional services or consultancy environment</li>\n  <li>Strong working knowledge of accounting principles, practices and procedures</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in using accounting software, such as Xero or MYOB</li>\n  <li>Excellent numerical and analytical skills, with a keen eye for detail</li>\n  <li>Effective communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to liaise with clients and stakeholders</li>\n  <li>Proactive, organised and able to work independently to meet deadlines</li>\n  <li>Relevant tertiary qualification in Accounting or a related field</li>\n</ul>",
